##Don't let rumors and attacks be the people's only power

| | Bai Qingyang

Only the living.

God bless the people who have finished eating, Zhang Chu.

The situation has reached a regrettable stage. Rumors, malice and vindictiveness fly all over the borderless cyber world, completely enveloping each individual's soul in the shadow.

Wake up in the morning, turn on your cell phone, the circle of friends is exhausting. Yesterday, Weibo disappeared from my phone; my circle of friends was a trap from which I could not escape.

The sudden double-whammy (I didn't even have time to understand the context) gives us a vivid picture of the power of the rumor (and, above all, of official collusion at first) . The exposure of the Wuhan Red Cross Society's many misdeeds has further angered the public. Once the fire burns, it spreads. In the course of inevitable collateral injury and wrong kill: first, the innocent crowd and the relevant people's name-calling, such as anger transferred to public intellectuals and many "people suspect conspirators" body; Second, shift the anger to the United States and the rest of the western capitalist world, claiming that the spread of the virus is part of their plot against China.

We could name a group of philosophers and wave their musty hardcover books that have languished in libraries for years, calling on the public to think "rationally" ; or we could jump out of the trap and hang our heads in the sand It is possible to mock the masses' ignorance and "earthiness" with pity, as a celebrity recently put it on twitter.

However, in the context of mass panic, it is hard to ask all individuals to think rationally. In the presence of reason, rumours and conspiracy theories still circulate among the people; How can we expect rumours, conspiracy theories and the ensuing malevolence to be contained in such a disorderly environment?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Is "punching hard" the best way to deal with rumors?

It's hard to judge a person in an environment where everyone is afraid of themselves. After all, rumor-mongering, rumor-mongering, and slander, are the only rights we have.

In his classic book, 1768, the renowned sinologist Philip A. Kuhn described it this way: 1

Read on and scroll down

"The great soul-stirring panic highlights to observers of Chinese society a particularly sad phenomenon: widespread hostility in the form of retaliation. In the birthplace of the so-called ghost... monks are trying to stir up fear of sorcery in order to scare away pilgrims from the rival temple. What's more, they made up a story that was easy to believe... it was a play within a play, and each play played on folk fears..

Once the government has launched a serious campaign against witchcraft, ordinary people have a good chance to settle old scores or for personal gain. It's a loaded weapon thrown out on the street for anyone... to use. In a society where power has always been scarce for ordinary people, vilifying others for 'soul-crying' has become a suddenly available power for ordinary people..

In such a troubled society, people doubt whether they can improve their situation through work or study. This situation is made all the more intolerable by a corrupt and irresponsible judicial system from which no civilian can expect fair compensation. In such a world, sorcery is both an illusion of power and a potential compensation for everyone's rights..."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Call the soul.

The reason I'm quoting soul is because Philip A. Kuhn's words are especially relevant today in 2020. It is true that rumors are flying around; it is true that people are fanatical about rumors; it is also true that people are attacking each other, hating each other, and hurting innocent people (accusations and invective against the Hubei Red Cross are beyond the scope of this article) .

The public knows nothing of the truth. They don't make a sound, and nothing bright or dark is ever going to change because of their voice. Everyone craves power. But, for a long time, the masses lacked it. And I don't mean only those "powers" as we know them -- like a farmer who was born and raised in Dundee, Scotland, and cast his own solemn vote for "Scottish independence from England. " . It should be a real power, a solemn power as a citizen and even a citizen of the world. It contains all the dignity of being a human being and its complete control over reason, knowledge and emotion. He is confident, happy, and fulfilled in the use of knowledge, reason, and emotion.

As we laugh and criticize people for spreading rumors and attacking each other, do we need to take a step back and think: What causes people to have a voice through these channels? Each and every one of us wants to exist. When the Yangguan Boulevard closed its doors to the masses, they would go free climbing on the cliffs. Free climbing ensures exposure, and they finally get the presence and the voice they want; but people on Sunway say: Crack Down on free climbing, because it's a serious threat to people's lives.

But it was the iron gate between the masses and the boulevard that drove people to the precipice in the first place.

We want the masses to "enlighten" , from the ignorance of easily believing rumors, just listen to one-sided words to hit the blind. However, what exactly is enlightenment? Enlightenment, Immanuel Kant says, is when people use their own efforts to get out of a "state of adolescence. " . This "minor" is an inability to use the "intellect" without the guidance of others. If the cause of one's "minor" is not lack of knowledge, but lack of determination and courage to use knowledge without guidance, this kind of "minor" will lead to ignorance. Two

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
What is enlightenment? The Enlightenment, according to The Antonio Gramsci of Italian thinkers, was one of The greatest manifestations of western discourse.

What causes the masses to "lack the determination and courage to use the intellect without guidance" ? What hangs between the masses and enlightenment, and is the greatest obstacle to unlocking the wisdom of the people?

Do not let precipice be the only place for the masses, just as do not let rumor-mongering and malicious slander be the only rights of the masses.
